вҠў parse-input
  given raw вүЎ "temperature: hot, humidity: 97%, wind: NNW 15mph"
  yield structured, confidence

  вҲҙ Parse В«rawВ» into a structured record with fields:
    temperature (numeric В°F), humidity (%), wind-speed (mph), wind-dir.
    Set В«confidenceВ» to how certain you are about the parse (0-100).

  вҠЁ structured has fields: temperature, humidity, wind-speed, wind-dir
  вҠЁ confidence вҲҲ [0, 100]
  вҠЁ temperature is numeric (В°F)

  вҠЁ? on failure:
    retry with В«oracle.failuresВ» appended to prompt
    max 2

  вҠЁ? on exhaustion:
    error-value(вҠҘ)

вҠў validate
  given parse-inputвҶ’structured
  given parse-inputвҶ’confidence
  yield validated, warnings[]

  вҲҙ Check В«structuredВ» for physically plausible values.
    Temperature between -100В°F and 150В°F, humidity 0-100%,
    wind-speed 0-300mph. Flag implausible values as В«warningsВ».
    If confidence < 50, add a low-confidence warning.

  вҠЁ validated is true if all values are physically plausible
  вҠЁ warnings contains one entry per implausible value

  given parse-inputвҶ’structured вҠҘ? skip with validated вүЎ false, warnings вүЎ ["upstream parse failed (вҠҘ)"]

вҠў forecast
  given validateвҶ’validated
  given validateвҶ’warnings
  given parse-inputвҶ’structured
  yield prediction, basis

  вҲҙ If В«validatedВ» is true, generate a weather В«predictionВ» for the next 6 hours
    based on В«structuredВ» data. Cite the input values as В«basisВ».
    If В«validatedВ» is false, generate a degraded prediction noting data quality issues.

  вҠЁ prediction is 1-3 sentences
  вҠЁ basis references at least 2 fields from structured data

  given parse-inputвҶ’structured вҠҘ? skip with prediction вүЎ "Unable to forecast: input parse failed", basis вүЎ "N/A"
  given validateвҶ’validated вҠҘ? skip with prediction вүЎ "Unable to forecast: validation failed", basis вүЎ "N/A"

вҠў format-output
  given forecastвҶ’prediction
  given forecastвҶ’basis
  given validateвҶ’warnings
  yield report

  вҠў= report вҶҗ "## Weather Forecast\n\n" ++
    prediction ++ "\n\n" ++
    "**Basis:** " ++ basis ++ "\n\n" ++
    (if warnings is empty then "" else "**Warnings:**\n" ++ join(warnings, "\n- "))

  вҠЁ report contains "Weather Forecast" header
  вҠЁ if warnings exist then report contains "Warnings" section
